  + [known_boundary] is conditional_or_open_frontier
  + [symbolic_fit] is closest formal analogue of "walk the space"
  + [next_question] is determine when traversal through a family actually produces cycles rather than detects constraints

& [Mechanism_004_MotivatedAbsoluteCycles] is a table row
  + [mechanism] is motivated cycles or absolute Hodge classes
  + [input_anchor] is highly stable Hodge-like class under comparison or motivic operations
  + [cycle_output] is substitute cycle object, not necessarily algebraic cycle
  + [construction_strength] is substitute
  + [known_boundary] is not_enough_for_Hodge_without_algebraicity
  + [symbolic_fit] is strong analogy to memory anchors but dangerous as proof
  + [next_question] is keep as periphery unless algebraicity bridge is supplied

& [Mechanism_005_ExplicitCycleSearch] is a table row
  + [mechanism] is explicit cycle construction on special hypersurfaces or families
  + [input_anchor] is candidate Hodge class plus geometric ansatz
  + [cycle_output] is explicit algebraic cycle when successful
  + [construction_strength] is special_case_or_heuristic
  + [known_boundary] is open_frontier_by_family
